{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"CORPUS-QUALITY FINDING (2026-07-15) — text-less findings excluded; adjudication corpus rebuilt.\n\nWhile preparing the human-adjudication worksheet, found that 61/400 sampled findings (15%) had an EMPTY `finding` statement — only metadata (location/severity/criteria) + a `verification` block, no prose. Root cause: finding PROSE (`finding`/`suggested_fix`) is persisted by `_slim` only since story 4e19/e344 (sidecar.py:441-446); review results written before that carry a leaner schema with no statement. Not recoverable (the text was never persisted, so a git-object walk can't recover it either).\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: a finding with no statement is NOT adjudicatable by ANY rater — an LLM or human judging TP/FP from location+criterion alone is guessing. Those 20/110 text-less rows in the double-labeled subset were almost certainly inflating disagreement (depressing kappa) with noise.\n\nFIX: build_adjudication_corpus.collect() now EXCLUDES findings with empty `finding` (documented inclusion rule + per-source exclusion count returned). Verified text-bearing population is ample: 15,821 surfaced + 10,850 dropped (excluded text-less: 2,592 surfaced + 708 dropped storewide), so the 300+100 targets and ≥280/≥90 floor still hold comfortably. Rebuilt the corpus as a clean seed-1729 stratified sample of the text-bearing population (300 surfaced + 100 dropped, 0 text-less, all rows carry a statement). Cost: the filtered population reshuffled the deterministic sample (only 4/400 rows overlapped the prior draw), so the ~500 prior LLM labels are largely sunk and a full re-label is running — accepted as the price of a correct, adjudicatable corpus.\n\nALSO FIXED en route: (1) adjudicate.py max_tokens 400->2000 — opus-4-8/sonnet-5 think by default and a 400-cap was fully consumed by thinking (stop_reason=max_tokens, thinking_tokens=399) before any text emitted, silently failing ~15% of rows (this, not rate-limiting, was the persistent-failure cause); (2) cluster_disputes classify bug — rows outside the double-labeled subset (rater_b blank) were mis-flagged as 'soft disputes'; a dispute now requires BOTH raters to have judged the row."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784172760900681001,"uuid":"7df258f5-a8c8-42f4-a469-16859e46798c"}